choices.text:
death !

– a quote from a British tourist visiting Italy and being chased by the waiter to pay the bill, about our all-loved late Italians etiquette, lojja di incominciare sempre 30 minuti dopo l’orario previsto (= to start every meal at least 30 minutes later than the scheduled time).

Anyway die hard antipasto addicts chose few selection of tapas – i.e. traditional ovum, snails and potato pancake with tuna and asparagus (my favourite) to balance the pasta madness.

PIZZA NOSTRA PIENA – after another work of art, topped with everything from tuna, yummy pimento, onions, pepperoni, melodious Proscuti pulled off Italian fridge, rocket and ricotta cheese, my birthday got pizzaed off. My words “YUM!

Ok Mama, Garderobe is less then 25! Not many days, so here we go enjoy soup, antipasto, pasta, pizza and crème shower – we are just warming up!

HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO ME! Soon you will find me in the actual shower, but Crunchy Breakfast in cute trinket box and lovely postcard from the Trinidad Kipling have warmed me up already!

È NATA!

…anyway no Tina or Jazz, that’s all I can say!

Of particular note by Natasha…

Lots of lovely recap for anyone chilling on 26th August – from World Humanitarian Summit to International Day
